{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Most dynamical formation channels allow a larger fraction of unequal-mass systems than isolated binary evolution (e.g.",
    "Di Carlo et al. 2019; Arca Sedda et al. 2020; Torniamenti et al. 2022).",
    "In particular, BBHs born from hierarchical mergers have a strong preference for unequal-mass mergers (Rodriguez et al. 2019; Fragione & Silk 2020; Zevin & Holz 2022).",
    "However, recent studies show that hierarchical mergers cannot account for the majority of LVK events (Zevin & Holz 2022; Fishbach et al. 2022).",
    "Recently, Santoliquido et al. (2023) showed that metal-poor and metal-free BBH mergers tend to have q ∼ 0.7 at redshift z 5 (see their Fig. 7)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Di Carlo et al. 2019; Arca Sedda et al. 2020; Torniamenti et al. 2022).",
